    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Given that there's some push back on the PR that implements this (https://github.com/status-im/status-go/pull/2999), how would everyone feel about just having 1) and 2) as a requirement for a \"Join community\" label?\r\n\r\nI don't know. IMO it may still be confusing to the user to see \"Join community\".\r\n\r\nI would opt to always have \"Request to join\" instead. We should probably adapt our community settings to show \"Auto accept requests\" rather than \"Request to join required\". It will align better with what we really do and we will avoid confusion and edge cases.\r\n\r\n> We shouldn't forget that, even if some node receives a signal that the owner node is online, and we change the label to \"Join community\", there's no guarantee that the owner node is still online by the time the user this that button.\r\n\r\nExactly.",
